<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,460,667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[189,423,496,522]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[189,423,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Lilium wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was segregated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Wallace (1891: 442)" authorityName="Wallace" authorityPageNumber="442" authorityYear="1891" box="[688,1113,496,522]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosanum">
<emphasis box="[688,863,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">L. formosanum</emphasis>
Wallace (1891: 442)
</taxonomicName>
based on the former having segmented bulb scales (Peng &amp; Li 1990). According to the authors, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[936,1118,532,558]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[936,1118,532,558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to south 
<collectingRegion box="[1366,1452,533,559]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(southwest 
<collectingCountry box="[265,337,568,595]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">China</collectingCountry>
). Based on the 
<typeStatus box="[507,605,568,594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[756,984,568,594]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[756,984,568,594]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Lilium wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
housed at KUN (Peng 89-1!), the species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[254,368,604,630]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis box="[254,368,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">L. brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This seems reasonable because 
<taxonomicName box="[731,845,604,630]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis box="[731,845,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">L. brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide range in 
<collectingCountry box="[1069,1136,604,630]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">China</collectingCountry>
and a sympatric distribution with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[193,370,640,666]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[193,370,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wallace" authorityYear="1891" box="[446,616,640,666]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosanum">
<emphasis box="[446,616,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">L. formosanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[779,861,640,666]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Liang, S. Y. &amp; Tamura, M." box="[875,1130,640,667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" pagination="24" refId="ref7281" refString="Liang, S. Y. &amp; Tamura, M. (2000) Lilium L .. In: Wu, Z. Y. &amp; Raven, P. H. (eds.) Flora of China 24. Science Press, Beijing; &amp; Missouri" type="book chapter" year="2000">Liang &amp; Tamura 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J." box="[1141,1330,640,667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" pagination="443 - 460" refId="ref7112" refString="Gao, Y. D., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. (2013 a) Evolutionary events in Lilium (including Nomocharis, Liliaceae) are temporally correlated with orogenies of the Q - T plateau and the HDM. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 68: 443 - 460. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2013.04.026" type="journal article" year="2013">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[1194,1243,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">et al</emphasis>
. 2013a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142423" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5142423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142423/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" startId="1.[136,229,1978,2000]" targetBox="[173,1405,712,1945]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1978,2072]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,247,1978,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. Bulbs of 
<taxonomicName box="[346,488,1978,1999]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis box="[346,488,1978,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Lilium brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from different populations showing variable segmentation of the scales. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1184,1225,1978,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">A-B</emphasis>
, Materials representing populations from Nanchuan, Chongqing (Gao G2010001, SZ) showing segmented (A) and unsegmented (B) scales, respectively; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1428,1445,2014,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">C</emphasis>
, Jiangyou, Sichuan (WJ10051401, SZ); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[515,532,2050,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">D</emphasis>
, Lushui, Yunnan (Gao G2009002, SZ).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
The main reason to question the species rank of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[726,903,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[726,903,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the key feature used to erect it. The articulated bulb scales described in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[414,592,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[414,592,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in many natural populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1226,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis box="[1110,1226,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1334,194,220]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">China</collectingCountry>
, including within some populations that exhibit both articulated and non-articulated bulbs (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1113,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1978,2000]" captionTargetBox="[173,1405,712,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-175@1.[151,1436,688,1953]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Bulbs of Lilium brownii from different populations showing variable segmentation of the scales. A-B, Materials representing populations from Nanchuan, Chongqing (Gao G2010001, SZ) showing segmented (A) and unsegmented (B) scales, respectively; C, Jiangyou, Sichuan (WJ10051401, SZ); D, Lushui, Yunnan (Gao G2009002, SZ)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142423/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Thus, the bulb scale feature cannot be used to distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[484,665,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[484,665,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[739,858,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis box="[739,858,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, molecular phylogenetic analyses of the internal transcribed spacer (ITS) (
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Hohenegger, M. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. &amp; Wan, J." box="[512,688,302,329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="69 - 85" refId="ref7024" refString="Gao, Y. D., Hohenegger, M., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D., He, X. J. &amp; Wan, J. (2012) A new species in the genus Nomocharis Franchet (Liliaceae): evidence that brings the genus Nomocharis into Lilium. Plant Systematics and Evolution 298: 69 - 85. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 011 - 0524 - 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[567,616,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J." box="[699,769,302,328]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="443 - 460" refId="ref7112" refString="Gao, Y. D., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. (2013 a) Evolutionary events in Lilium (including Nomocharis, Liliaceae) are temporally correlated with orogenies of the Q - T plateau and the HDM. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 68: 443 - 460. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2013.04.026" type="journal article" year="2013">2013a</bibRefCitation>
, b) also suggest that there is no boundary between 
<taxonomicName box="[1336,1451,302,328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis box="[1336,1451,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[187,368,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[187,368,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on molecular phylogeny and continuous variation of the bulb scale characteristic, we propose that only one taxon should be recognized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
Another reason to question the status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[671,852,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[671,852,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the source of type specimen. Only the 
<typeStatus box="[1353,1451,410,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen exists, and it was prepared from an accession of unknown origin in cultivation at Kunming Botanical Garden. Thus, the native habitat of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[438,616,482,508]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[438,616,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown, and the original authors did not investigate individuals other than the type. Concerns over the type specimen may further support our assertions that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; F. X. Li" authorityYear="1990" box="[1201,1380,518,544]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis box="[1201,1380,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not deserving a recognition as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
